mr. forbes can apply to the scottish court of chivalry in edinburgh for a coat of arms, which i think he is going to do,'' harold brooks-baker, publishing director of the british bluebloods' guide, said wednesday
the title is connected to land in aberdeenshire and mr. forbes can call himself malcom forbes of barnes _ which i think would be the more elegant _ or forbes of barnis-forbes or baron forbes of barnes,'' brooks-baker said
i do not intend to use the title,'' the aberdeen press and journal quoted forbes as saying. ``my father was born there (in aberdeenshire) in 1880. i thought it would be great to have the title back in the forbes family where it originated.''
domino's pizza magnate tom monaghan plans to open his collection of more than $30 million worth of frank lloyd wright creations to the public this week
monaghan, president of domino's and owner of the detroit tigers, said he has been ``evangelizing'' about the architect for more than 40 years, so ``it seems natural for me to open the first museum devoted to his work.''
monaghan has assembled a huge collection of wright buildings, drawings, designs, furniture, ceramics, decorative sculpture and glass in less than four years
monaghan's holdings include some 400 objects and considerable archival materials that belonged to wright, who died in 1959
this week, he is inaugurating the national center for the study of frank lloyd wright with a symposium beginning today and a public opening of the museum saturday
