i was shaking,'' said daugherty, adding he yelled for the gunman to get out of the store. ``he didn't say a word. i think he was probably as scared as i was.''
the gunman ran out, virtually into the arms of a police officer who had spotted him earlier as a possible robbery suspect and radioed for help. detective carl oestreich ordered the man to drop his gun, but the suspect continued to run
