last year, the government paid around $700 million to service its foreign debt
officials in santo domingo say part of the reason for this caribbean nation's economic slump is the cut in the u.s. quota for dominican sugar, this nation's most important export
the u.s. quota for dominican sugar now is 160,000 tons compared to 525,000 tons in 1983
u.s. aid to the dominican republic is $150 million. the republic also receives an additional $35 million annually in surplus food
traveling with balaguer will be the u.s. ambassador to the dominican republic, lowell kilday, and 10 government officials, according to reid cabral. balaquer will stay at the home of the dominican ambassador, jose leon asencio, while in washington
