the environmental protection agency has ordered general motors corp. to recall almost half a million 1985 cars and light trucks sold under the chevrolet, pontiac and gmc nameplates, epa said today
the cars exceed federal standards for carbon monoxide exhaust emissions and for evaporated gasoline, epa said
such orders are rare and are generally a sign the agency and the manufacturer could not agree on something, such as the cause of the problem, its scope, the necessary repair or terms of the recall. most recalls are made voluntarily
gm's washington office said the company would have a statement later
the company has 45 days either to request a public hearing to contest the order, or to submit a repair plan for epa's approval before notices are mailed to owners
epa said the affected vehicles are equipped with 5.0-liter (305 cubic inches) and 5.7-liter (350 cubic inches) engines and were sold as the chevrolet impala, caprice classic, camaro, monte carlo and el camino; the pontiac firebird, bonneville, grand prix and parisienne; and the gmc caballero. models sold in california, which are built to stricter standards, are included
the excessive emissions are in part the result of defects in a thermal vacuum switch in the evaporation control system, epa said. but the agency said simple replacement of the switch may not completely remedy the problem and further repairs, which it did not specify, may be necessary
last year, gm recalled more than a million vehicles from the 1982 and 1983 model years for similar problems
gm also is recalling about 4,900 1988 chevrolet corvettes to fix defective wheel welds that could cause the wheel center to separate from the rim during braking or cornering
the automaker said wednesday it is also recalling about 460 1987 gmc and chevrolet full-size vans to correct fuel tank filler pipes that could cause fuel to leak during refueling or turning
no accidents or injuries have been linked to either problem, gm said. vehicle owners are being notified of the recall by dealers, who will correct the problems at no charge, the company said
the corvettes, all equipped with 17-inch wheels, may be missing a weld on some wheels, gm said. the condition could result in partial loss of steering control and a sudden changed in vehicle direction, the automaker said. passenger and flight attendants' reaction; pick up 16th pvs, `the new ...'</note>
major u.s. airlines have no immediate plans to match northwest airlines' bold new move to ban smoking on most of its flights, and some industry analysts say the carriers are unlikely to do so
northwest, the nation's fifth-largest airline, announced wednesday it will prohibit smoking on all its domestic flights except those to and from hawaii and on some foreign routes
the ban makes minneapolis-based northwest the first major u.s. airline to mandate a smoke-free environment in the air. it goes beyond federal regulations that will outlaw smoking on all domestic flights of two hours or less beginning april 23
northwest said its prohibition was a response to passenger and employee requests. a.b. ``sky'' magary, northwest's executive vice president for marketing, told a news conference in new york that while the policy is not without risk, ``we believe more nonsmokers will switch to northwest than smokers will leave.''
wall street seemed unimpressed by northwest's smoke-free innovation. the airline's stock closed on the new york stock exchange at $45.75 a share, down 12{ cents from tuesday
some analysts believe northwest risks chasing away potential passengers, and other big airlines appear reluctant to follow the carrier's lead
we have no plans to follow that move,'' said mary o'neill, a spokeswoman for no. 2 american airlines. recent surveys conducted by american indicated a significant segment of people who want to smoke on planes, despite a growing demand for smoke-free areas, she said
american and several other big airlines contacted wednesday stressed that they planned to establish no-smoking policies in line with the new federal law
under those rules, passengers who insist on lighting up will face civil fines of as much as $1,000, and fliers who tamper with smoke alarms in airplane lavatories face up to $2,000 in penalties
we are ready to implement our no-smoking policy ... in line with the federal law,'' said united airlines spokesman dan sheehy. united, the nation's largest airline, has had a smoking ban in place since jan. 1 on all its flights within california, in accordance with a state law
fourth-ranked delta air lines has garnered a lot of support for its own california smoking ban, spokesman jim lundy said
he said delta's reaction to northwest's move was ``really tough to call,'' but did not rule out further action by his airline
we will of course take a look at what northwest is doing and see if we want to make an adjustment to our program,'' lundy said
anthony hatch, an airline analyst for argus research corp., said he did not expect the other carriers to match northwest's policy
it's a gutsy move and most airlines don't make gutsy moves,'' hatch said. ``it could alienate some people.''
three smokers, who were waiting to depart on northwest flights wednesday from minneapolis-st. paul international airport, said they don't object to the carrier's new smoking ban
it's probably a good idea,'' janice davis, a boston real estate broker, told the st. paul pioneer press dispatch. ``i can get by without smoking.''
even some northwest flight attendants, who are smokers, told the newspaper the new policy might help them quit smoking
the new policy, called ``northwest clears the air,'' will take effect april 23, the same day as the new federal regulations. it will apply to flights within the contiguous 48 states and flights to and from alaska, mexico, canada, jamaica and the cayman islands
the longest flights covered by the smoking ban are four or five hours, according to the airline. about 30 percent of northwest's domestic flights and about 20 percent of all domestic flights last more than the two-hour duration covered by the new federal smoking regulations
northwest flights to and from hawaii and overseas will continue offering smoking sections because those flights ``carry a greater proportion of foreign passengers who feel differently about the issue,'' the airline stated
we still have (foreign) competitors that are handing out cigars to passengers on board,'' magary said
but even that could be changing. air u.k. ltd., a small british airline that flies to destinations in britain and western europe, is banning smoking on all its flights effective next sunday
and a spokesman in london for british airways plc, one of the world's largest airlines, said the carrier was looking ``quite seriously'' at the possibility of banning smoking on both short and long flights
the trend also has appeared in southwest asia. government-controlled singapore airlines unveiled plans wednesday to introduce the first no-smoking commercial flights in the region next month
smoking will be barred on four of the 14 daily shuttle flights between singapore and kuala lumpur, the capital of neighboring malaysia, starting april 4. the trip takes about 45 minutes
